      "label": "Conceptual",
      "marks_per_q": 1,
      "count": 20,
      "questions": [
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch01_A_001",
          "text": "The additive identity for rational numbers is:",
          "options": {
            "a": "1",
            "b": "-1",
            "c": "0",
            "d": "1/2"
          },
          "correct": "c",
          "difficulty": "easy",
          "source": "ncert",
          "explanation": "Adding 0 to any rational number gives the same number. So 0 is the additive identity."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch01_A_002",
          "text": "The multiplicative inverse of -7/9 is:",
          "options": {
            "a": "7/9",
            "b": "-9/7",
            "c": "9/7",
            "d": "-7/9"
          },
          "correct": "b",
          "difficulty": "easy",
          "source": "ncert",
          "explanation": "The multiplicative inverse (reciprocal) of -7/9 is -9/7 because (-7/9) × (-9/7) = 63/63 = 1."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch01_A_003",
          "text": "(-5/8) + (5/8) = ?",
          "options": {
            "a": "1",
            "b": "-1",
            "c": "0",
            "d": "10/8"
          },
          "correct": "c",
          "difficulty": "easy",
          "source": "ncert",
          "explanation": "(-5/8) + (5/8) = 0. These are additive inverses of each other."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch01_A_004",
          "text": "Which property is shown by: (2/3) × (4/5 + 1/3) = (2/3 × 4/5) + (2/3 × 1/3)?",
          "options": {
            "a": "Commutative property",
            "b": "Associative property",
            "c": "Distributive property of multiplication over addition",
            "d": "Closure property"
          },
          "correct": "c",
          "difficulty": "easy",
          "source": "ncert_exemplar",
          "explanation": "a × (b + c) = a×b + a×c is the Distributive property of multiplication over addition."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch01_A_005",
          "text": "The rational number -3/5 lies between:",
          "options": {
            "a": "0 and 1",
            "b": "-1 and 0",
            "c": "-1 and -2",
            "d": "1 and 2"
          },
          "correct": "b",
          "difficulty": "easy",
          "source": "ncert",
          "explanation": "-3/5 = -0.6, which lies between -1 and 0 on the number line."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch01_A_006",
          "text": "Which of the following shows the commutative property of addition for rational numbers?",
          "options": {
            "a": "(1/2 + 1/3) + 1/4 = 1/2 + (1/3 + 1/4)",
            "b": "1/2 + 1/3 = 1/3 + 1/2",
            "c": "1/2 × (1/3 + 1/4) = 1/2 × 1/3 + 1/2 × 1/4",
            "d": "1/2 + 0 = 1/2"
          },
          "correct": "b",
          "difficulty": "easy",
          "source": "ncert_exemplar",
          "explanation": "Commutative property of addition: a + b = b + a. Here 1/2 + 1/3 = 1/3 + 1/2."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch01_A_007",
          "text": "The product of any non-zero rational number and its multiplicative inverse is always:",
          "options": {
            "a": "0",
            "b": "-1",
            "c": "the number itself",
            "d": "1"
          },
          "correct": "d",
          "difficulty": "easy",
          "source": "ncert",
          "explanation": "By definition, a × (1/a) = 1 for any non-zero rational number a."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch01_A_008",
          "text": "Which of the following rational numbers is in standard form?",
          "options": {
            "a": "12/18",
            "b": "-4/10",
            "c": "15/(-25)",
            "d": "-3/7"
          },
          "correct": "d",
          "difficulty": "easy",
          "source": "ncert",
          "explanation": "-3/7 is in standard form: denominator is positive, and HCF(3,7) = 1. Others can be simplified further."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch01_A_009",
          "text": "Between any two different rational numbers, there exist:",
          "options": {
            "a": "exactly one rational number",
            "b": "exactly ten rational numbers",
            "c": "infinitely many rational numbers",
            "d": "no rational number"
          },
          "correct": "c",
          "difficulty": "easy",
          "source": "ncert_exemplar",
          "explanation": "Rational numbers are dense — between any two rational numbers, infinitely many rational numbers exist."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch01_A_010",
          "text": "The additive inverse of -11/13 is:",
          "options": {
            "a": "13/11",
            "b": "11/13",
            "c": "-13/11",
            "d": "-11/13"
          },
          "correct": "b",
          "difficulty": "easy",
          "source": "ncert",
          "explanation": "Additive inverse of -11/13 is 11/13 because (-11/13) + (11/13) = 0."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch01_A_011",
          "text": "(-3/4) × (-4/3) = ?",
          "options": {
            "a": "-1",
            "b": "1",
            "c": "0",
            "d": "9/16"
          },
          "correct": "b",
          "difficulty": "easy",
          "source": "ncert",
          "explanation": "(-3/4) × (-4/3) = 12/12 = 1. These are multiplicative inverses of each other."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch01_A_012",
          "text": "Which of the following illustrates associative property of multiplication?",
          "options": {
            "a": "1/2 × 1/3 = 1/3 × 1/2",
            "b": "(1/2 × 1/3) × 1/4 = 1/2 × (1/3 × 1/4)",
            "c": "1/2 × (1/3 + 1/4) = 1/2 × 1/3 + 1/2 × 1/4",
            "d": "1/2 × 1 = 1/2"
          },
          "correct": "b",
          "difficulty": "easy",
          "source": "ncert_exemplar",
          "explanation": "Associative property of multiplication: (a × b) × c = a × (b × c)."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch01_A_013",
          "text": "The only rational number that is its own additive inverse is:",
          "options": {
            "a": "1",
            "b": "-1",
            "c": "0",
            "d": "1/2"
          },
          "correct": "c",
          "difficulty": "easy",
          "source": "ncert",
          "explanation": "0 + 0 = 0, so 0 is its own additive inverse."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch01_A_014",
          "text": "(-8/15) ÷ (4/5) = ?",
          "options": {
            "a": "-2/3",
            "b": "2/3",
            "c": "-32/75",
            "d": "-3/2"
          },
          "correct": "a",
          "difficulty": "easy",
          "source": "kv_paper",
          "explanation": "(-8/15) ÷ (4/5) = (-8/15) × (5/4) = -40/60 = -2/3."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch01_A_015",
          "text": "Rational numbers are closed under which of the following operations?",
          "options": {
            "a": "Division only",
            "b": "Addition only",
            "c": "Addition, subtraction and multiplication",
            "d": "All four operations including division by zero"
          },
          "correct": "c",
          "difficulty": "easy",
          "source": "ncert",
          "explanation": "Rational numbers are closed under addition, subtraction, and multiplication. Division by zero is undefined."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch01_A_016",
          "text": "The standard form of -36/(-48) is:",
          "options": {
            "a": "3/4",
            "b": "-3/4",
            "c": "36/48",
            "d": "-36/-48"
          },
          "correct": "a",
          "difficulty": "easy",
          "source": "ncert",
          "explanation": "-36/(-48) = 36/48. HCF(36,48) = 12. So 36/48 = 3/4. Denominator is positive, fraction is in lowest terms."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch01_A_017",
          "text": "Which of the following is NOT a rational number?",
          "options": {
            "a": "0",
            "b": "-5",
            "c": "3/0",
            "d": "-2/3"
          },
          "correct": "c",
          "difficulty": "easy",
          "source": "ncert",
          "explanation": "A rational number is of the form p/q where q ≠ 0. In 3/0, the denominator is 0, so it is not a rational number."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch01_A_018",
          "text": "(5/7) + (-5/7) = ?",
          "options": {
            "a": "10/7",
            "b": "0",
            "c": "1",
            "d": "-1"
          },
          "correct": "b",
          "difficulty": "easy",
          "source": "ncert",
          "explanation": "5/7 and -5/7 are additive inverses. Their sum = 0."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch01_A_019",
          "text": "The reciprocal of -1 is:",
          "options": {
            "a": "1",
            "b": "-1",
            "c": "0",
            "d": "undefined"
          },
          "correct": "b",
          "difficulty": "easy",
          "source": "ncert",
          "explanation": "Reciprocal of -1 = 1/(-1) = -1. Verification: (-1) × (-1) = 1. ✓"
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch01_A_020",
          "text": "Which property states that a × (b + c) = a × b + a × c for rational numbers?",
          "options": {
            "a": "Associative property of multiplication",
            "b": "Commutative property of multiplication",
            "c": "Distributive property of multiplication over addition",
            "d": "Closure property"
          },
          "correct": "c",
          "difficulty": "easy",
          "source": "ncert",
          "explanation": "The distributive property links multiplication and addition: a × (b + c) = a×b + a×c."
        }
      ]
    },
    "B": {
      "type": "mcq",
      "label": "Application",
      "marks_per_q": 2,
      "count": 10,
      "questions": [
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch01_B_001",
          "text": "Using appropriate properties, find: (3/7) × (-5/11) + (3/7) × (-6/11)",
          "options": {
            "a": "-3/7",
            "b": "3/7",
            "c": "-33/77",
            "d": "33/77"
          },
          "correct": "a",
          "difficulty": "medium",
          "source": "ncert_exemplar",
          "explanation": "Take 3/7 common: (3/7) × (-5/11 + -6/11) = (3/7) × (-11/11) = (3/7) × (-1) = -3/7."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch01_B_002",
          "text": "What should be added to (-3/8) to get 1/4?",
          "options": {
            "a": "-5/8",
            "b": "5/8",
            "c": "1/8",
            "d": "-1/8"
          },
          "correct": "b",
          "difficulty": "medium",
          "source": "kv_paper",
          "explanation": "Let x + (-3/8) = 1/4. So x = 1/4 + 3/8 = 2/8 + 3/8 = 5/8."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch01_B_003",
          "text": "Simplify: (4/9) ÷ (-2/3) × (3/4) - (-1/6)",
          "options": {
            "a": "-1/3",
            "b": "1/3",
            "c": "-1/6",
            "d": "1/6"
          },
          "correct": "a",
          "difficulty": "medium",
          "source": "kv_paper",
          "explanation": "= (4/9) × (-3/2) × (3/4) + 1/6 = (-2/3) × (3/4) + 1/6 = -1/2 + 1/6 = -3/6 + 1/6 = -2/6 = -1/3."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch01_B_004",
          "text": "Find: (2/3) + (-3/5) + (1/6) + (-7/10)",
          "options": {
            "a": "-7/15",
            "b": "7/15",
            "c": "-14/30",
            "d": "7/30"
          },
          "correct": "a",
          "difficulty": "medium",
          "source": "cbse_sample",
          "explanation": "LCM(3,5,6,10) = 30. = 20/30 - 18/30 + 5/30 - 21/30 = (20-18+5-21)/30 = -14/30 = -7/15."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch01_B_005",
          "text": "A shopkeeper gains ₹(3/4) on each kg of sugar sold. He sells 16⅔ kg in a day. What is his total gain?",
          "options": {
            "a": "₹12.50",
            "b": "₹10.50",
            "c": "₹15.00",
            "d": "₹8.50"
          },
          "correct": "a",
          "difficulty": "medium",
          "source": "mp_birla",
          "explanation": "16⅔ = 50/3 kg. Gain = 3/4 × 50/3 = 150/12 = 25/2 = ₹12.50."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch01_B_006",
          "text": "Find the value of x if: x × (-3/7) = -6/35",
          "options": {
            "a": "2/5",
            "b": "-2/5",
            "c": "18/245",
            "d": "2/35"
          },
          "correct": "a",
          "difficulty": "medium",
          "source": "kv_paper",
          "explanation": "x = (-6/35) ÷ (-3/7) = (-6/35) × (-7/3) = 42/105 = 2/5."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch01_B_007",
          "text": "The rational number -5/3 lies between which two consecutive integers?",
          "options": {
            "a": "-1 and -2",
            "b": "0 and -1",
            "c": "1 and 2",
            "d": "-2 and -3"
          },
          "correct": "a",
          "difficulty": "medium",
          "source": "ncert",
          "explanation": "-5/3 = -1.667. This lies between -2 and -1. So it lies between the consecutive integers -2 and -1."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch01_B_008",
          "text": "Which of the following pairs are NOT multiplicative inverses of each other?",
          "options": {
            "a": "5/7 and 7/5",
            "b": "-3/4 and -4/3",
            "c": "1 and 1",
            "d": "-2/3 and 3/2"
          },
          "correct": "d",
          "difficulty": "medium",
          "source": "ncert_exemplar",
          "explanation": "(-2/3) × (3/2) = -1 ≠ 1. So they are NOT multiplicative inverses. All other pairs multiply to give 1."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch01_B_009",
          "text": "The sum of two rational numbers is -1/3. If one number is 5/6, find the other.",
          "options": {
            "a": "-7/6",
            "b": "7/6",
            "c": "-1/2",
            "d": "1/2"
          },
          "correct": "a",
          "difficulty": "medium",
          "source": "cbse_sample",
          "explanation": "x + 5/6 = -1/3. So x = -1/3 - 5/6 = -2/6 - 5/6 = -7/6."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch01_B_010",
          "text": "Which of the following is the correct ascending order of: -3/4, -5/8, -1/2, -7/12?",
          "options": {
            "a": "-3/4 < -5/8 < -7/12 < -1/2",
            "b": "-1/2 < -7/12 < -5/8 < -3/4",
            "c": "-3/4 < -7/12 < -5/8 < -1/2",
            "d": "-1/2 < -5/8 < -7/12 < -3/4"
          },
          "correct": "a",
          "difficulty": "medium",
          "source": "mp_birla",
          "explanation": "Convert to 24ths: -3/4 = -18/24, -5/8 = -15/24, -7/12 = -14/24, -1/2 = -12/24. Ascending: -18 < -15 < -14 < -12. So: -3/4 < -5/8 < -7/12 < -1/2."
        }
      ]
    },
    "C": {
      "type": "mcq",
      "label": "Higher Order",
      "marks_per_q": 3,
      "count": 6,
      "questions": [
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch01_C_001",
          "text": "Using distributive property, simplify: (-5/8) × (3/7) + (-5/8) × (4/7) + (-5/8) × (-7/7)",
          "options": {
            "a": "-5/8",
            "b": "5/8",
            "c": "0",
            "d": "1"
          },
          "correct": "c",
          "difficulty": "hard",
          "source": "ncert_exemplar",
          "explanation": "Factor out -5/8: = (-5/8) × (3/7 + 4/7 - 7/7) = (-5/8) × (7/7 - 7/7) = (-5/8) × 0 = 0."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch01_C_002",
          "text": "If p = 2/3, q = -3/4 and r = 5/6, then p × (q + r) equals:",
          "options": {
            "a": "1/18, which demonstrates associative property",
            "b": "1/18, which demonstrates distributive property",
            "c": "1/6, which demonstrates distributive property",
            "d": "-1/18, which demonstrates distributive property"
          },
          "correct": "b",
          "difficulty": "hard",
          "source": "ncert_exemplar",
          "explanation": "q + r = -3/4 + 5/6 = -9/12 + 10/12 = 1/12. p × (q+r) = 2/3 × 1/12 = 2/36 = 1/18. This demonstrates the distributive property."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch01_C_003",
          "text": "Ravi walks 5/6 km east, then 3/4 km west, then 1/3 km east. His final position from the start is:",
          "options": {
            "a": "5/12 km west",
            "b": "5/12 km east",
            "c": "1/4 km east",
            "d": "1/12 km east"
          },
          "correct": "b",
          "difficulty": "hard",
          "source": "mp_birla",
          "explanation": "Taking east as positive: 5/6 - 3/4 + 1/3. LCM = 12. = 10/12 - 9/12 + 4/12 = 5/12 km east."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch01_C_004",
          "text": "A water tank is 3/5 full. After 1/4 of its total capacity is used, what fraction of the tank is empty?",
          "options": {
            "a": "7/20",
            "b": "13/20",
            "c": "3/20",
            "d": "17/20"
          },
          "correct": "b",
          "difficulty": "hard",
          "source": "kv_paper",
          "explanation": "Water remaining = 3/5 - 1/4 = 12/20 - 5/20 = 7/20. Empty fraction = 1 - 7/20 = 13/20."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch01_C_005",
          "text": "Which set of three rational numbers correctly lies between -2/3 and 3/4?",
          "options": {
            "a": "-7/12, 0, 7/12",
            "b": "-8/12, 0, 9/12",
            "c": "-1, 0, 1",
            "d": "-3/4, 0, 4/5"
          },
          "correct": "a",
          "difficulty": "hard",
          "source": "ncert_exemplar",
          "explanation": "-2/3 = -8/12 and 3/4 = 9/12. -7/12 > -8/12 ✓, 0 is between ✓, 7/12 < 9/12 ✓. Option b includes endpoints. Option c and d go outside range."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch01_C_006",
          "text": "A man spends 1/3 of his salary on food, 1/4 on rent, and 1/6 on transport. What fraction of his salary is he left with?",
          "options": {
            "a": "1/4",
            "b": "3/12",
            "c": "1/6",
            "d": "5/12"
          },
          "correct": "a",
          "difficulty": "hard",
          "source": "cbse_sample",
          "explanation": "Spent = 1/3 + 1/4 + 1/6. LCM = 12. = 4/12 + 3/12 + 2/12 = 9/12 = 3/4. Left = 1 - 3/4 = 1/4."
        }
      ]
    },
    "D": {
      "type": "direct_input",
      "label": "Numerical",
      "marks_per_q": 3,
      "count": 10,
      "questions": [
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch01_D_001",
          "text": "Find the value of: (5/6) × (-3/10) + (5/6) × (-7/10). Use distributive property.",
          "correct_answer": "-5/6",
          "answer_type": "fraction",
          "accepted_forms": ["-5/6", "-0.833", "-0.83"],
          "difficulty": "medium",
          "source": "ncert_exemplar",
          "explanation": "Factor 5/6: = (5/6) × (-3/10 + -7/10) = (5/6) × (-10/10) = (5/6) × (-1) = -5/6."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch01_D_002",
          "text": "Subtract (-4/9) from (2/3). Write your answer as a fraction in simplest form.",
          "correct_answer": "10/9",
          "answer_type": "fraction",
          "accepted_forms": ["10/9", "1 1/9"],
          "difficulty": "medium",
          "source": "ncert",
          "explanation": "(2/3) - (-4/9) = 2/3 + 4/9 = 6/9 + 4/9 = 10/9."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch01_D_003",
          "text": "Find the value of: [(-3/4) + (1/2)] × [(-2/3) + (5/6)]",
          "correct_answer": "-1/24",
          "answer_type": "fraction",
          "accepted_forms": ["-1/24", "-0.0416", "-0.042"],
          "difficulty": "medium",
          "source": "kv_paper",
          "explanation": "First bracket: -3/4 + 2/4 = -1/4. Second bracket: -4/6 + 5/6 = 1/6. Result: (-1/4) × (1/6) = -1/24."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch01_D_004",
          "text": "Find the sum of the additive inverse of (5/12) and the multiplicative inverse of (-4/3).",
          "correct_answer": "-7/6",
          "answer_type": "fraction",
          "accepted_forms": ["-7/6", "-1 1/6", "-1.166", "-1.17"],
          "difficulty": "medium",
          "source": "ncert_exemplar",
          "explanation": "Additive inverse of 5/12 = -5/12. Multiplicative inverse of -4/3 = -3/4. Sum = -5/12 + (-3/4) = -5/12 - 9/12 = -14/12 = -7/6."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch01_D_005",
          "text": "Simplify: (7/12) ÷ (-7/6) × (-3/14). Write your answer as a fraction in simplest form.",
          "correct_answer": "3/28",
          "answer_type": "fraction",
          "accepted_forms": ["3/28", "0.107", "0.11"],
          "difficulty": "medium",
          "source": "kv_paper",
          "explanation": "= (7/12) × (-6/7) × (-3/14) = (-42/84) × (-3/14) = (-1/2) × (-3/14) = 3/28."
        },
        {
          "id": "cbse_8_ch01_D_006",
          "text": "A rope of length 15/4 m is cut into pieces each of length 3/8 m. How many pieces are obtained?",
